28/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament endorsed on Wednesday (December 27th) a government decision to deploy 127 Macedonian troops to the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan and 21 to the EU's Althea mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). 
This will be the 9th rotation in Afghanistan and the second in BiH. 
In a speech to parliament, Defence Minister Lazar Elenovski stressed that Macedonia is committed to participating in such international operations, both to boost efforts to join NATO and to make the military more professional. 
(Vecer, MRT - 28/12/06)
